ğŸ§ . How do you secure sensitive data in Jenkins?
  Use the Credentials plugin to store sensitive data securely and integrate with external secret managers.Jenkins secures sensitive data using the Credentials plugin, which
  stores passwords, keys, and tokens encrypted and allows jobs to access them securely via environment variables without exposing them in the pipeline

